<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758220>
    dc:description "Figs. 1-4. Perlodes spp., frequency (% of sample) of particular relative wing-lengths (RWL = WL/HCW) in males and females. 1. P. microcephalus. 2. P. microcephalus (?) from Medingen, N. Germany. 3. P. dispar. 4. P. mortoni. Figures in legends are the numbers of specimens measured; compare text for origin of samples." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758220/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758224>
    dc:description "Fig 5. Perlodes spp., sclerite platelets on periphery of anchor disc of German P. microcephalus (River Fulda at Ried), P. dispar (River Fulda nr Schlitz), and Scottish P. mortoni. mo-1 to mo-7 show individual ♀♀, most from River Tweed, mo-2 from River Dee. There are 5 ♀♀ similar to mo-3 (including one from River Tay), 4 ♀♀ are similar to mo-6, 5 ♀♀ (rivers Tweed and Dee) are similar to mo-7. Orientation (centre of anchor disc is towards right hand side) and scale same for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758224/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

